JDBC used for retrieve data and update data
JDBC is the industry standard for database independent connectivity between the Java programming language
and a wide range of databases
Java application -->JDBC API -->JDBC Driver Manager --> oracle, sql , mysql
3 Important Steps in JDBC
-first:--> Connection: helps our java project connect to database
-second:--> Statement: Helps to write and execute SQL query
-third: ResultSet-->  A Data structure where we can store the data that came from database
(Update)-->INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, ALTER, TRUNCATE, DROP statements
